      "src": "photography/outdoors/outdoors01.jpg",
      "alt": "Blood Moon",
      "title": "Blood Moon",
      "description": "The term “blood moon” refers to its reddish orange appearance, occurring during a total lunar eclipse. When the earth passes between the sun and moon, the little sunlight not blocked by the earth managing to reach the lunar surface is filtered through the edges of the Earth’s atmosphere. 🌎 While Earth’s air molecules scatter most of the blue (shorter) wavelengths of light, reddish tones (longer wavelengths) are left behind reflecting off of the moon and casting a red glow that makes it appear red.",
      "date": "March 14, 2025",
      "location": "",
      "camera": "📸 The moon godess’s Canon EOS Rebel t6 🌒"
